import requests

Loading an image through the matplotlib.image module¶

In [3]:
# URL of the image
url = "https://tractive.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/puppy-care-guide-for-new-parents.jpg"

# Fetch the image from the URL
response = requests.get(url)

if response.status_code == 200:
    img_plot = Image.open(BytesIO(response.content))  # Open image using PIL
    img_array = np.array(img_plot)  # Convert to NumPy array
    
    # Display the image
    plt.imshow(img_array)
    plt.axis('off')  # Hide axes
    plt.show()
else:
    print("Failed to retrieve image")
In [4]:
# Print the type
print(type(img_array))

<class 'numpy.ndarray'>
In [5]:

print("Shape:", img_array.shape)  # (Height, Width, Channels)

Shape: (1365, 2048, 3)

Resizing the image using Pillow¶

In [8]:
url = "https://tractive.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/puppy-care-guide-for-new-parents.jpg"
response = requests.get(url)

if response.status_code == 200:
    img = Image.open(BytesIO(response.content))  # Open image from bytes
    img.show()  # Display the image
else:
    print("Failed to retrieve image")
In [9]:
img_resized = img.resize((200, 200))  # Resize image to 200x200 pixels
In [10]:
# Display the image
plt.imshow(img_resized)
plt.axis('off')  # Hide axes
plt.show()
In [11]:
print(np.array(img_resized).shape)  # Convert to NumPy array and print shape

(200, 200, 3)

Converting RGB image to Grayscale image using OpenCV¶

In [12]:
# Importing Open CV library
import cv2
In [13]:
# URL of the image
url = "https://tractive.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/puppy-care-guide-for-new-parents.jpg"
In [14]:
# Fetch the image from the URL
response = requests.get(url)
img_array = np.asarray(bytearray(response.content), dtype=np.uint8)
img = cv2.imdecode(img_array, cv2.IMREAD_COLOR)
In [15]:
# Convert to grayscale
gray_img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
In [16]:
# Display the grayscale image
plt.imshow(gray_img, cmap='gray')
plt.axis('off')  # Hide axes
plt.show()
In [17]:
# Convert grayscale image to NumPy array
gray_array = np.array(gray_img)
In [18]:
# Print type
print("Type:", type(gray_array))

Type: <class 'numpy.ndarray'>
In [19]:

print("Shape:", gray_array.shape)
